PROMPT 1 :

As a senior Java Developer, create a springboot project, where controller are generated using swagger-codegen-maven-
plugin and specific folder structure where swagger json will go.
For each Swagger JSON/OpenAPI spec added to this project, generation will create:
Controller/service API contracts (endpoint signatures)
RequestVO classes for request payloads
ResponseVO classes for response payloads
Mainly focus on Search flights → Book ticket → View booking → Cancel booking.
controller/
├── FlightController.java
├── BookingController.java
└── HealthController.java
• Use Spring Boot and Java
• Single application instance (no distributed systems concerns)
• No authentication, authorization, or rate limiting
• No flight search or destination logic
• Assume the client already knows the flight number
• Use in-memory storage only (no database required)
• Ensure flights cannot be overbooked
• Only implement booking APIs (no retrieval endpoints required)
• Use appropriate HTTP methods and status codes
